From 2880c4834e4e4aee25ea90a3a864766e0aaeaf99 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 18:11:13 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] On-Prem AWS + SQL Server template: cloud-aware DB sizing, new
 API route, new UI module

- onprem_sizer.py (new): cloud x DB sizing matrix. AWS self-hosted EC2
  (AMD EPYC first, BYOL + AWS-owned Enterprise license for SQL Server,
  automatic fallback if AMD unavailable in region). GCP managed-equivalent
  (Cloud SQL custom tier, N2D/AMD-first). Kubeadm/OpenShift generic
  self-hosted VM sizing. Reuses aws_machine_catalog/gcp_machine_catalog
  (read-only) for instance selection.

- api_server.py: new POST /api/generate-onprem-estimate route, fully
  separate from /api/generate-estimate (SaaS). Sizing only, pricing=None
  always. Reuses excel_handler/node_distributor/excel_exporter read-only.
  Zero lines changed in the existing SaaS route (221 insertions, 0
  deletions in this file).

- frontend/src/app/onprem/estimate/new + onprem/results (new routes):
  on-prem sizing wizard (cloud + DB + volumes) and sizing-only results
  page with echarts visuals (worker role donut, compute-shape bars,
  storage bars, DB sizing card with AMD selection note). No cost figures
  anywhere in this module.

- lib/api.ts: added onpremApi + types, additive only (91 insertions, 0
  deletions).

- Sidebar.tsx: added 'On-Premise Sizing' nav entry, additive only (39
  insertions, 0 deletions).

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, eslint clean on all new/changed files,
full next build succeeds (15 routes incl. 2 new), end-to-end pipeline
test run (real LibreOffice recalculation + real Excel sizing workbook
generation) for AWS + SQL Server in ap-south-1 (AMD selected) and
us-west-1 (no AMD, correct fallback). SaaS path untouched: 0 deletions
across all 3 modified files.
